---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About Us">
	<section
		class="py-32 lg:py-52 bg-[#050505] flex items-center justify-center min-h-[60vh] border-b border-white/5"
	>
		<div class="container mx-auto px-6 text-center">
			<h1
				class="text-5xl lg:text-7xl font-black text-white tracking-tighter uppercase leading-[0.9] mb-8"
			>
				NOT MOTIVATION.<br /><span class="text-primary-600"
					>SYSTEMS.</span
				>
			</h1>
			<p
				class="text-2xl text-gray-400 font-light max-w-2xl mx-auto italic border-l-2 border-primary-600 pl-6 text-left"
			>
				"We do not rise to the level of our goals. We fall to the level
				of our systems."
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="py-32 bg-[#080808]">
		<div class="container mx-auto px-6 max-w-4xl">
			<h2
				class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-white mb-12 uppercase tracking-wide border-b border-primary-600/30 pb-4 inline-block"
			>
				The Mission
			</h2>
			<div
				class="prose prose-invert prose-xl text-gray-400 leading-relaxed font-light"
			>
				<p>
					The Inner Fire was not created to make you feel good. It was
					created to make you effective. Specifically, effective at
					building the kind of life that most men dream of but few
					possess the discipline to construct.
				</p>
				<p>
					Look around you. We are living in an era of unprecedented
					comfort and unprecedented weakness. The modern world is an
					engineered dopamine casino, designed by billionaires to hook
					your attention, drain your testosterone, and sediment your
					ambition. Scrolling, binge-watching, junk food, cheap
					pleasure—these are not random accidents. They are weapons in
					a war for your potential.
				</p>
				<p>
					Most men are losing this war. They are drifting through
					life, medicating their anxiety with cheap entertainment, and
					wondering why they feel empty despite being "safe" and
					"comfortable."
				</p>
				<p>
					Our mission is simple: <strong class="text-white"
						>To provide the antidote.</strong
					> We exist to drag you out of the seductive comfort of mediocrity
					and into the cold, clear air of high performance. We utilize biology,
					psychology, and social dynamics to build men who are dangerous
					to their enemies, valuable to their allies, and masters of themselves.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="py-32 bg-[#050505] border-y border-white/5">
		<div class="container mx-auto px-6 max-w-4xl">
			<div class="text-right mb-12">
				<h2
					class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-white uppercase tracking-wide border-b border-primary-600/30 pb-4 inline-block"
				>
					The System
				</h2>
			</div>
			<div
				class="prose prose-invert prose-xl text-gray-400 leading-relaxed font-light text-right"
			>
				<p>
					Motivation is garbage. It is a feeling, and feelings are
					fickle. You cannot build a legacy on how you "feel" on a
					Tuesday morning when it's raining and you're tired.
				</p>
				<p>
					The amateur relies on inspiration. The professional relies
					on systems. A system is a set of behaviors, protocols, and
					environments that make the desired outcome inevitable,
					regardless of how you feel.
				</p>
				<p>
					The Inner Fire is a comprehensive operating system for the
					male experience. We don't just tell you to "be confident"—we
					give you the specific social scripts and body language
					protocols that signal status. We don't just tell you to "get
					in shape"—we give you the exact rep schemes and
					macronutrient ratios that optimize hormonal output.
				</p>
				<p>
					We break down the vague concept of "Success" into concrete,
					actionable verticals: Health, Mindset, Social, Wealth, and
					Skill. Each of these is a machine. You are the mechanic. Our
					job is to hand you the wrench.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="py-32 bg-[#080808]">
		<div class="container mx-auto px-6 max-w-6xl">
			<div class="text-center mb-24">
				<h2
					class="text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-extrabold text-white mb-6 uppercase tracking-tight"
				>
					Our Methodology
				</h2>
				<p class="text-gray-500 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
					The algorithm for self-transcendence.
				</p>
			</div>

			<div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
				<div
					class="bg-[#050505] p-10 border-l-4 border-primary-600 relative overflow-hidden group hover:bg-[#0a0a0a] transition-colors"
				>
					<span
						class="absolute top-4 right-4 text-6xl font-black text-white/5 group-hover:text-primary-500/10 transition-colors"
						>01</span
					>
					<h3
						class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4 uppercase tracking-wider"
					>
						Analyze
					</h3>
					<p class="text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
						We strip a problem down to its first principles. We
						ignore tradition and dogma. We only ask: "What is the
						biological or psychological mechanism at play?"
					</p>
				</div>

				<div
					class="bg-[#050505] p-10 border-l-4 border-primary-600 relative overflow-hidden group hover:bg-[#0a0a0a] transition-colors"
				>
					<span
						class="absolute top-4 right-4 text-6xl font-black text-white/5 group-hover:text-primary-500/10 transition-colors"
						>02</span
					>
					<h3
						class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4 uppercase tracking-wider"
					>
						Optimize
					</h3>
					<p class="text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
						We design a protocol to exploit that mechanism. This is
						where scientific literature meets field testing. We
						formulate the "Minimum Effective Dose" for maximum
						results.
					</p>
				</div>

				<div
					class="bg-[#050505] p-10 border-l-4 border-primary-600 relative overflow-hidden group hover:bg-[#0a0a0a] transition-colors"
				>
					<span
						class="absolute top-4 right-4 text-6xl font-black text-white/5 group-hover:text-primary-500/10 transition-colors"
						>03</span
					>
					<h3
						class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4 uppercase tracking-wider"
					>
						Automate
					</h3>
					<p class="text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
						We turn the protocol into a habit. We build the
						environment so that adherence is automatic. Thinking is
						expensive; habits are free. We make excellence improved.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="py-40 bg-[#050505] border-t border-white/5">
		<div class="container mx-auto px-6 text-center">
			<h2
				class="text-5xl font-black text-white mb-10 tracking-tighter uppercase"
			>
				Are you <span class="text-primary-600">capable</span> of more?
			</h2>
			<a
				href="/"
				class="inline-block px-12 py-5 border border-white text-white hover:bg-white hover:text-black font-black uppercase tracking-[0.2em] transition-all duration-300 text-sm"
			>
				Enter The Protocol
			</a>
		</div>
	</section>
</BaseLayout>
